just_use parity_check.py

# label: BUGGY (stale paths — needs retargeting)
# role: agent tool — Go↔Elm twin-module export drift detector

Compares exported names between paired Go and Elm LynRummy
modules. Catches structural drift (renames, new exports on
one side, removed exports) at near-zero cost. Does NOT catch
semantic drift — that's what the conformance DSL fixtures
are for.

## Known-stale (FIRM)

`GO_ROOT` points to `angry-gopher/lynrummy/` and `ELM_ROOT`
points to `angry-gopher/elm-lynrummy/src/LynRummy/`. Both
paths NO LONGER EXIST after the repo reorg. Current
locations:

- Go: `games/lynrummy/`
- Elm: `games/lynrummy/elm-port-docs/src/LynRummy/`

The tool will fail-fast with "no such directory" until the
roots are updated. A small fix, but someone needs to check
the MODULE_PAIRS map too — paired module names likely still
match, but verify.

## Surface (pre-fix)

- `python3 tools/parity_check.py` — check all pairs.
- `python3 tools/parity_check.py <pair_name>` — check one.

## Companion

`tools/parity_ignore.py` holds the known-deliberate
divergences to subtract before reporting. Co-stale.

## Pointers

- Sidecar drift detection (different mechanism, sidecars-only)
  at `showell/claude_writings/drift_detection_from_sidecars*.md`.
- Conformance DSL fixtures: `games/lynrummy/conformance/`.
